  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study is a double-masked, randomized, placebo-controlled study of the safety and
      preliminary efficacy of ATG003 (topical mecamylamine) in patients receiving maintenance
      injections of either ranibizumab or bevacizumab. Study Hypothesis: Mecamylamine could be
      effective in the treatment of neovascular AMD.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
